After removing outliers, we can see that the graphs provide much more information. For example we can see that the columns 'numer_of_reviews' and 'reviews_per_month' follow an exponential distribution while all other numerical features follow a multimodal distribution, which makes sense since there are underlying groups in the dataset.

Let's also remove the outliers from the price column, as most of the listings have a price range of 40-200. We remove these listings for better predictions.

the r2 score is the proportion of the variance in the dependent variable that is predictable from the independent variable(s) The mean squared error of a model is the mean of the squared prediction errors over all instances in the test set.

These are the 2 most important metrics for evaluating this model.

These scores make sense due to the low correlation of your features.

This only seems to make the model worse as, both the mean squared error and the r2 score are worse. However we can see that most actual and predicted vales are in a similar price range. I will group the prices into groups in order to try improve the model.

K-nearest neighbours (KNN)¶

In [30]:
price_cat_limits = [
    (data['price'] <= 50),
    (data['price'] > 50) & (data['price'] <=75),
    (data['price'] >75) & (data['price'] <= 100),
    (data['price'] >100) & (data['price'] <= 150),
    (data['price'] >150) & (data['price'] <= 200)
]
price_cat = ['<50','50-75','75-100','100-150','150-200']
data['price_range'] = np.select(price_cat_limits,price_cat)

We can see that this model has a much higher accuracy at 98,6%. This makes sense as when we tried to predict the actual prices we were not far off usually.

Conclusion¶

By using the KNN model and changing the target variable into price range categories, we were able to achieve a very good score. In my opinion this way of predicting price ranges instead of the actual price is the best way to go since the goal of this project, is to help approximate the potential cost of getting an Airbnb or renting one out. With these price ranges being divided into smaller categories like <50, 50-75, 75-100 etc. the user will still have a good estimate of the price they can expect from an airbnb listing.
